    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nExtends `benchmarks/tune_ex2_emu.py` with two improvements needed for tuning the hd256 forward kernel on B200 (SM100).\r\n\r\n### hd256 sweep support\r\n\r\nThe hd256 softmax loop steps `k` by 2 (rather than 1), so `k % freq` only takes even values. As a result, `ex2_emu_res` cannot be inferred from `freq` alone — it must be swept independently to explore distinct hardware-vs-emulated `exp2` ratios.\r\n\r\nChanges:\r\n- Phase 1 adds `ex2_emu_res` as a third sweep axis for hd256 keys (on top of the existing `ex2_emu_freq × ex2_emu_start_frg` grid).\r\n- Phase 2 (register count sweep) is skipped for hd256: `num_regs_other` is fixed at 32 in the hd256 kernel, and the 512-budget formula used for smaller head dims does not apply.\r\n\r\n### GPU clock lock/unlock\r\n\r\nBenchmark variability from frequency scaling can obscure small performance differences during tuning. The script now locks clocks to the hardware maximum at startup and restores them on exit.\r\n\r\nChanges:\r\n- `setup_clocks(do_lock)` locks GPU clocks at startup and registers `unlock_clocks()` via `atexit`, so clocks are restored even if the script is interrupted mid-sweep.\r\n- `--lock-clocks` / `--no-lock-clocks` CLI flag (default: `--lock-clocks`).\r\n- Falls back to a printed warning when locking is unavailable.\r\n- Skips `sudo` when already running as root (for example, inside containers).\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\n- [ ] `ruff check benchmarks/tune_ex2_emu.py` — no issues\r\n- [ ] `ruff format benchmarks/tune_ex2_emu.py --check` — already formatted\r\n- [x] Parse/patch round-trip: `parse_tuning_config` → `patch_config` → re-parse yields identical dict\r\n- [x] `_query_clocks` returns `(current_mhz, max_mhz)` on multi-GPU machines (uses the first GPU only)\r\n- [x] `_nvidia_smi_cmd` omits `sudo` when `os.geteuid() == 0`\r\n- [x] `setup_clocks(False)` prints a warning when clocks are below max\r\n- [x] `setup_clocks(True)` locks clocks and prints confirmation\r\n- [x] `python benchmarks/tune_ex2_emu.py --headdim 256 --seqlen 8192` completes the full sweep on B200\r\n\r\n",
